	 <h2>Upgrade to KDE SC 4.7.4 packages<img src="../images/download_64.png" style="float:right; margin:-8px 0 0 0;" alt="Install KDE 4 Debian packages in your hard disk" /></h2>

	 <p style="margin-bottom:0.1em;">
		There are 4.7.4 packages available in experimental, you can upgrade your KDE SC to 4.7.4 both from the 4.6.5 packages in Debian sid and 
		from the KDE SC 4.7.2 packages formerly available at <a href="http://qt-kde.debian.net/"><code>qt-kde.debian.net</code></a>, you can
		do the upgrade thusly:
	 <br /><br />

	 <p style="margin-bottom:0.1em;">
		1. Add the experimental repository to your sources.list:
	 <br />

	 <p style="margin-bottom:0.1em;">
		# Replace 'xx' or the whole url to use your local mirror.
	 <br />
		deb http://ftp.xx.debian.org/debian/ experimental main
	 <br />
		deb-src http://ftp.xx.debian.org/debian/ experimental main
	 <br /><br />

	 <p style="margin-bottom:0.1em;">
		2. Download <a href="files/kde-experimental"><code>this file</code></a> and save it as /etc/apt/preferences.d/kde-experimental, beware if you
		already an /etc/apt/preferences or you have other files in /etc/apt/preferences.d/, if that's your case you should read you apt
		preferences files and understand well what you are doing. In any case, you can do "man apt_preferences" to find more information 
		about apt pinning.
	 <br /><br />

	 <p style="margin-bottom:0.1em;">
		3. Just upgrade your system with "apt-get update && apt-get dist-upgrade" or "aptitude update && aptitude dist-upgrade".
	 <br /><br />


